I use it. Very little overhead on the CPU. No Container files. Great 
support from the author on CIS. Gets between 50-68% compression. I use it 
on HPFS because of the smaller allocation unit. It will only compress if 
you take more than one unit (makes sense). It says it works on floppies too 
(for backups) but I have not tried that yet. The only 'problem' I have is 
the compressed drive letter (the compression can be done for a whole drive 
or a set of paths; my phisical drive D: is accessible as D: uncompressed 
and as G: as compressed/expanded) is thought to be a LAN drive (mountable) 
and I don't have a LAN.

